%pyspark
import pandas as pd
import re
import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
url = 'https://drive.google.com/uc?export=download&id=1gRtCuJv4sj8-9uATuPuWbz7TEknPDHo8'

data = pd.read_csv(url)

print(data.describe())

%pyspark

res_data = data.copy()
#grouped = res_data.groupby(['dog_type'])['dog_type'].count().reset_index(name='counts')
res_data['dog_type'] = res_data['dog_type'].str.replace('-', '').str.replace(' or ', ',').str.replace('+', ',').str.replace(' + ', ',').str.replace('mix','' ).str.replace('–',',').str.replace(', ',',').str.replace(' And',',').str.replace(' , ',',').replace('Bulls','bull').replace('bulls','bull').str.replace(' & ',',').str.replace(' / ',',').str.replace('Bulldogs','Bulldog')


# Phân tách các giá trị ra thành các dòng riêng biệt
for index in range(len(res_data)):
    res_data['dog_type'][index] = res_data['dog_type'][index].strip().title()
    
res_data['dog_type'] = res_data['dog_type'].str.split(',')
res_data = res_data.explode('dog_type')

# XU LY SO
# tìm kiếm số trong chuỗi dog_type và gán vào cột counts
res_data['counts'] = res_data['dog_type'].str.extract(r'(\d+)', expand=False)

# chuyển giá trị NaN thành 1 trong cột counts
res_data['counts'] = res_data['counts'].fillna(1)
res_data = pd.concat([res_data['dog_type'], res_data['counts']], axis=1)

#Xoá phần số trong chuỗi 
res_data['dog_type'] = res_data['dog_type'].str.replace(r'\s*\(\d+\)\s*', '', regex=True)
res_data['dog_type'] = res_data['dog_type'].str.replace(r'\s*\[\d+\]\s*', '', regex=True)
res_data['dog_type'] = res_data['dog_type'].str.replace(r'\s*\[\d+\+]\s*', '', regex=True)
res_data['dog_type'] = res_data['dog_type'].str.replace(r'\s*\(\d+\,\)\s*', '', regex=True)
res_data['dog_type'] = res_data['dog_type'].str.replace(r'\s*\d+\s*', '', regex=True)

#    #res_data['dog_type'][index] = res_data['dog_type'][index].strip().title()
res_data['dog_type'] = res_data['dog_type'].str.replace('Pit Bull \(', 'Pit Bull', regex=True)
res_data['dog_type'] = res_data['dog_type'].str.replace('Pit Bull ', 'Pit Bull', regex=True)
res_data['dog_type'] = res_data['dog_type'].str.replace('Pit Bulls', 'Pit Bull', regex=True)
res_data['dog_type'] = res_data['dog_type'].str.replace('\)', 'other', regex=True)

# doi ten nhom others
#res_data['dog_type_cleaned'] = res_data['dog_type'].str.lower().str.replace(r'<|pack of|Pack Of Dogshallo', 'other')
res_data['dog_type'] = res_data['dog_type'].apply(lambda x: 'other' if ('<' in x or 'pack of' in x.lower()) else x)
res_data['counts'] = res_data['counts'].astype(int)

res_data = res_data.groupby(['dog_type'])['counts'].sum().reset_index(name='counts')
res_data['dog_type'][0] = 'other'
res_data = res_data.groupby(['dog_type'])['counts'].sum().reset_index(name='counts')
# cong 
#res_data = res_data.groupby(['dog_type'])['counts'].sum().reset_index(name='counts')

#res_data.groupby(['dog_type'])['counts'].sum().reset_index(name = 'count')
print(res_data)
#res_data.to_excel('D:/kq.xlsx', index=False)
plt.pie(res_data['counts'], labels=res_data['dog_type'])
plt.show()

%pyspark
class Attack_case:
    def __init__(self, date, year, city, state, vic_name, vic_age, dog_type, desc):
        self.date = date
        self.year = year
        self.city = city
        self.state = state
        self.vic_name = vic_name
        self.vic_age = vic_age
        self.dog_type = dog_type
        self.desc = desc
attack_cases = []
for _, row in data.iterrows():
    attack_case = Attack_case(
        row['date'],
        row['year'],
        row['city'],
        row['state'],
        row['vic_name'],
        row['vic_age'],
        row['dog_type'],
        row['desc']
    )
    attack_cases.append(attack_case)
